President Biden recently held a virtual meeting with business, university, and healthcare leaders who have implemented COVID-19 vaccination requirements for their employees. The President expressed his gratitude for their efforts in protecting their workforce and communities. He also highlighted the vaccination requirements for federal healthcare workers and service members. The leaders discussed their decision-making process and plans for implementing vaccination requirements. President Biden encouraged them to share their experiences with others in their industries and expressed his hope that more employers would follow suit. The federal government will continue to support employers in implementing COVID-19 vaccination requirements.